# Copy to .env.local and fill in. NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars are baked into the static
# build and exposed to the browser — this is expected for an OAuth client_id
# (it is public by design; there is no client secret in this flow).
#
# Create the client_id in Google Cloud Console:
#   APIs & Services > Credentials > Create credentials > OAuth client ID
#   Application type: "Web application"
#   Authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:3000 and your deployed origin
#   Enable the Gmail API, and on the OAuth consent screen (Testing) add your
#   users as test users. Scope used by the app: gmail.readonly
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
